{"Date": "2019-04-09 13:11:59", "content": "<p>\n</p> <p>In this week\u2019s podcast our editors meet <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Juan</span> <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Manuel</span> <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Santo</span>s, the former president of <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Colombia</span>\n</p> <p>\n</p> <p>\n</p> <p>ANNE MCELVOY asks <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Juan</span> <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Manuel</span> <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Santo</span>s, the former president of <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Colombia</span>, whether the country can <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">sustain</span> a lasting peace with the left-wing FARC <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">guerrilla</span> group. They discuss the best way to <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">tackle</span> the global drug trade and why <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Venezuela</span>\u2019s <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">dictator</span>, Nicol\u00e1s Maduro, needs a \u201cgolden bridge\u201d to give up power peacefully.\n</p> <p>\n</p> <p>Listen on:  Apple Podcasts  |  Spotify \u00a0|  Google \u00a0|\u00a0 <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Stitcher</span> \u00a0|\u00a0 TuneIn \n</p> <p>\n</p> <p>  Correction (April 7th 2019):\u00a0 An earlier version of the <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">rubric</span> for this piece referred to <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Juan</span> <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Manuel</span> <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Santo</span>s as the former prime minister of Italy. He is in fact the former president of <span class=\"word-wrap-span\">Colombia</span>. This has been corrected. Sorry.\u00a0 </p>", "Last": "2019_4_9_3.json", "Next": "2019_4_9_5.json", "assistent": {"Colombia": {"ex": ["n. \u54e5\u4f26\u6bd4\u4e9a\uff1b\u3010\u56fd\u3011\u54e5\u4f26\u6bd4\u4e9a\uff1b\u54e5\u4f26\u6bd4\u4e9a\u5171\u548c\u56fd", "\u7f51\u7edc \u54e5\u4f26\u6bd4\u4e9a\u5496\u5561\uff1b\u54e5\u4f26\u6bd4\u4e9a\u5236\u9020\uff1b\u6ce2\u54e5\u5927"], "pron": {"peg": "\u82f1\u00a0[k\u02